1. CREATE three dictionaries:
   - room_numbers: maps course numbers to room numbers
   - instructors: maps course numbers to instructor names
   - meeting_times: maps course numbers to meeting times

2. PROMPT user to enter a course number
3. CONVERT input to uppercase to handle case sensitivity
4. CHECK if course number exists in any dictionary
5. IF course exists:
   - DISPLAY room number, instructor, and meeting time
6. ELSE:
   - DISPLAY error message
7. IMPLEMENT loop to allow multiple queries until user chooses to exit
